[2]
Date: Sun 21 Jan 2007
From: Dan Silver <dgsilver@yahoo.com>
Source: Xinhua News Agency Report [trans. by sender, edited]
<http://news.cctv.com/china/20070121/101662.shtml>

China (Guangzhou): reports of 10-plus cases of unknown infectious disease
denied
-----------------------------------------------
Recent reports from outside press state that there have appeared 10-plus
patients infected with an undiagnosed infectious disease. An official from
Guangzhou's Department of Health has clarified that Guangzhou has not
discovered an unknown infectious disease and that the reports from outside
are untrue.
Outside press has also reported that all the patients are undergoing
treatment at Guangzhou No. 8 People's Hospital. In response to this, the
spokesperson and vice director of Guangzhou's Department of Health, Yuanda
Xiong, stated on Sun 21 Jan 2007 that these were unfounded rumors. No
undiagnosed infectious disease has appeared in Guangzhou.
The director of Guangzhou No. 8 People's Hospital also stated that, since
the beginning of January 2007, the hospital has not admitted any patients
with epidemic or undiagnosed illness whatsoever. Guangzhou has no
extraordinary circumstances whatsoever. At the moment, the majority of
patients in the hospital are being treated for liver illness, some with
AIDS and recognized illnesses. Aside from these, there are a few patients
with malaria. Talk of so-called "undiagnosed infectious disease" is
complete nonsense.
[byline: Xia Yang]
--
Dan Silver
